body:
Firstly, I'm MojoBubu {{champion:17}} 
{{item:1082}}SILVER SOLO/DUO{{item:1082}}
{{item:3400}} GOLD FLEX{{item:3400}}

Was gold plat last season (sort of partial to this post).

This isn't my first time playing at the start of a season. It seems likely there is a {{summoner:4}}  of players, new and old every new season. 
What I'm most fascinated by the amount of people who give up. Stems from frustration, sure. It's like people look for reasons to rage. Even when we're winning. 

(Spams pings, Sits near tower, Spam types about a miss play)
 ^ granted we're winning here, if we had been behind he would have {{summoner:6}}  his way to the base.

Okay so, above is a particular example, but I've played about 50 ranked games this season. I've noted roughly 50% of games someone is afking. (I haven't tally'd) It feels higher than normal. I was playing quite a lot about a month ago, took a break after hitting platinum waited for season. I feel like its the new season to blame for the surge of players and granted higher anxiety about placements / promos. It is just ridiculous. I find myself reporting every other game, sometimes games back to back. Yes back to back afkers. (I know I'm not alone, I've read enough posts about the same thing in the past). There is a correlation between new season and perhaps rank tiers? People in gold / getting knocked down with silver bronze players. You have skill gap differences that trigger people causing them to quit or any other reason you can think of that happens when skill gapped players are mashed up together. I understand I can climb out, but at this point it feels like such matchmaking RNG. Do I get a griefing afker.

(P.S. Are reports working? No notifications for these acutal inting afkers or even verbal abusers. I think riot is asleep, maybe they need extra help? Why not bring back the tribunal, Honor 5 players get to join tribunal maybe? Help weed through this barrage of griefing/toxic/afking/trolls)
